4.
    a.
        An advantage of using solar power rather than fossil fuels is that it is renewable, so we will never run out. Another advantage is that it does not produce, as a direct consequence of operation, any greenhouse gases, which contribute to global warming and environmental damage. This is in contrast to fossil fuels which are not renewable, and produce carbon dioxide, a greenhouse gas. However, solar power does not work in places with low sun exposure, or when it is at night; and, solar power is less energy-dense than fossil fuels, and requires a lot more land to produce power.
    b.
        In direct current, the flow of electricity and movement of electrons is in one direction only. In alternating current, it continually changes directions tens of times per second.
