            Because white color means it reflects a broader spectrum of electromagnetic radiation, meaning it absorbs less of it. Since the sun heats up spacecraft via electromagnetic radiation, and we don't want the spacecraft to heat up, it is painted white.
        ii?
            This is because air is not a good conductor, as air particles are spread far apart, and as to transfer heat air particles must collide, and as their sparseness means that collisions are low. There is a caveat that circulation allows fast transfer of heat in air by allowing the high-energy particles to directly transfer their energy to another object. So, small pockets of trapped air are used to reduce circulation and to leverage air's insulating property.
