7.
    a. (?)
        We can find the shape of the magnetic field produced by the loop of wire by plotting some (at least three each) random points around the two places where the wire pierces the card, and then taking a compass, and for each point place the compass on the point, and then move it slightly in the direction which the compass is pointing, away from the wire, and then plotting that point and repeating; and then when the compass has either gone off the card or reached some notable end-point (the wire), drawing a line through the points and marking an arrow on the line facing what the compass claims to be north. This will show the shape of the magnetic field.

    b? counter-clockwise circular arrows around left wire; clockwise circular arrows around right wire; at least three arrows pointing straight up and somewhat curving between them; spacing of field lines increases further from wires
    c.
        i.
            A
        ii.
            There is no effect on the direction of the force on the cross-section of the wire when the direction of current in the loop is reversed as when the direction of current in the loop is reversed, the direction of the magnetic field is also reversed. This "cancels out" the change in direction of the current vis-a-vis direction of force.
